The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 27: The government is likely to table a bill in the ongoing Parliament session to amend the Income Tax Act to exempt taxing of negative profits. The Prime Minister?s economic advisory council had last month given its nod to the proposal and directed the department of revenue to carry out the necessary amendment in the Act, official sources said. 

 New Delhi, Nov. 27: Azim Premji of Wipro is open to diluting his stake in the company from the current 81 per cent. This would be done to increase the company?s liquidity and make an acquisition using its stock, Premji said. He also said he would remain the chairman of the company at least for the next five years.

 New Delhi, Nov. 27: Power trading companies have accepted with cynicism regulator CERC?s proposal to fix a cap on profit margins to reduce the cost of traded power. The power-deficient states have welcomed the move. These states also want the regulator to fix a cap on the sale price of electricity.

 New Delhi, Nov. 27: Ranbaxy group company Fortis Healthcare today said it was planning an initial public offering next year to raise capital for its expansions.

 New Delhi, Nov. 27: The department of telecommunications may scale down BSNL?s Rs 1,840-crore interconnect usage charges demand on MTNL. It may also ask BSNL to reimburse Rs 30 crore to MTNL for using its network facilities between 2000 and 2005.




